Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and lightly crisped, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp Southwest Spice and 2 TBSP oil.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Dice a few slices until you have ¼ cup. Core, seed, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}. Core, seed, and chop @Roma tomato{1}. Zest @lime{1} until you have ½ tsp; cut lime into quarters. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat.

Place jalapeño, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt in a #small bowl{}. Squeeze in juice from 2 lime wedges. Toss to coat and set aside to marinate.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and 4 lime wedges.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

While veggies cook, toss together tomato, diced onion, cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice in a second small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. In a third small bowl, stir together @sour cream{2%tbsp}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}. Warm in #microwave{} until soft, about ~{30%seconds}. Divide tortillas between plates and fill with sweet potatoes, veggies, @pepper jack cheese{1%cup}, salsa, crema, and as much jalapeño as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.